#Ad One things for certain, Lourdes absolutely loves being a big sister! She wakes up in the morning anticipating what her baby brother Chancellor’s up to. From the moment we brought him home she’s been in love. So you can imagine how hard it is to tell her she can’t be in her baby brother’s face. With her attending school daily, and us finally being back together as a family after Chancellor’s RSV battle, I’m not taking any chances of him getting sick again, even if that means I keep them at a distance. Talk about hard… Explaining to your four year old that she can’t give her brother a kiss. It’s the hardest thing in the world to do, but so necessary this holiday season. With there being holiday parties and family gatherings coming up, I have to do my best to keep my little ones protected. 

If you have small children I’m urging you to try your best to keep them healthy this holiday season! Making sure your children are washing their hands regularly, wearing masks when necessary, and are up to date on all their childhood vaccines is so important this time of year! December 5th-9th is National Influenza Vaccination Week and my friends over over at @ivaccinatemi have a ton of information and resources available to help navigate through what vaccines are best for you and your family. The flu vaccine is safe, effective, and helps protect our family and our loved ones. If you haven’t gotten your flu shot yet, now’s the perfect time before the holidays. Head over to IVaccinate.org during National Influenza Vaccination Week for more information and data.

Cheers to a happy, healthy, and joyful holiday season! Staying well is the best gift you can give yourself and your family!

When I say that this big guy’s session has been a long time coming, I mean it’s been a LONG time coming.  His mama talked about doing newborn photos with me before she was even pregnant with him.  So, when I got the news that she was expecting, we were both so excited and eager to plan a special session. When he arrived, as a healthy and happy baby boy, I started counting down the days until I would finally meet him. Then, the unthinkable happened, and this poor boy got sick. He ended up in the hospital with RSV for nearly two whole weeks. His story is so emotional and scary, but thankfully it’s a story of triumph.  Despite the challenges he faced, he persevered and came out so strong and happy on the other side. 🙌🏻
After that, we waited as he received vaccinations and allowed his immune system to grow stronger, which left us here. At nearly three months old, mom was longing for a chance to capture sweet newborn photos, and we were both anxious that we were running out of time.
Newborn photos are typically captured within the first few weeks after baby arrives, so at eleven weeks old, we thought we had our work cut out for us.  When he arrived at my studio and smiled at me with those round cheeks and beautiful dark eyes, I knew we couldn’t go wrong with whatever we captured. The session went beautifully. We had to change some plans along the way, but we got everything that mom had hoped for, for so long, and more. I could not have asked for anything better from his much anticipated newborn-ish session. I’m so in love with him. 🥹🥰

#Ad As busy parents to two children under 5, there can be so many unknown threats to having a safe and enjoyable time with our family outside the home. 
 
From juggling school, extracurricular activities, birthday parties, spending time with friends and loved ones, it can be difficult navigating where, when, and how to keep our children safe from illnesses and germs that cause all the terrible viruses going around day to day. 
 
So as we continue to live our daily lives spending time with other family and close friends, we are making sure that we take the proper precautions to stay healthy and safe. It’s no secret that our family chooses to vaccinate and trust the science provided to Michigan parents. Sure like anything, choosing to vaccinate our family can come with questions and concerns, so we depend on healthcare providers and @ivaccinatemi to help us navigate all of our questions and concerns surrounding all vaccines! To protect against serious illness, we choose to get the flu shot each year to avoid the headache of one less illness that could put our family’s activities on hold. The flu vaccine is safe, effective, and helps protect yourself and your family. It’s not too late, you can still get your flu vaccine! As we near the end of the winter season, we want to continue to stay protected the best way we can! Being healthy and ready to enjoy the spring ahead is our number one priority!

I’ve been in a funk the last few days… And I’ve come to the realization as a mom and wife, I rarely do things for myself, and I rarely feel appreciated for the things I do. Even though I know my family appreciates me, it sometimes doesn’t feel that way when they expect me to do things I always do. Keeping the house clean, caring for an infant, helping a Pre-K toddler with homework and sight words, trying to not let the never ending to-do list pile up in my brain, the list goes on and on… Sometimes I don’t want to do anything except care for myself. And as a mom, you feel guilty for having those thoughts.

I now recognize that, that’s an indication that I need to insert more me time, and self care into my daily routine and schedule. It’s easy for me to recognize I’m in a funk, so the change starts today. I will be maintaining weekly self care days and times of day. I have to find my own peace again.

#Ad Being a mother of two has truly been an adjustment, especially having a school aged child and an infant to care for. Two totally different stages of life with their own set of things for me to be concerned about. It feels like every other day, I’m trying to keep one child from getting the other sick. We all know kids are a little walking, talking molecules of germs! Now especially with the world being back to some semblance of normality, it’s still my job as a mother to keep them both healthy and protected. With Lourdes going to school and enjoying her regular activities daily, attending birthday parties, traveling and spending time with loved ones, exposure to COVID-19 is always on my mind. That is why I make it a priority to have my family test for COVID-19 regularly. Frequent testing is key in reducing the spread of disease and exposure to others in the household and fellow classmates, school staff, family and friends. If you’re having issues keeping up with obtaining COVID-19 testing kits, all households in the state of Michigan can order free COVID-19 tests through AccessCovidTests.org. Yup that’s right, Michigan residents still have access to free tests through @michiganhhs . Did you also know that private health insurers are required to cover up to eight at-home COVID-19 tests per month for each person covered by a health plan? So be sure to check with your insurer for the most up-to-date information for your specific plan.

For more information about testing, visit Michigan.gov/COVIDtest

Let’s continue to work to stay healthy and keep our children healthy as well!
